Program: Outlook
Title: 04/07/2011
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/p00hk3j2
Last Broadcast Date: Tue 5 Jul 2011
Extraordinary personal stories from around the world. today, the former child soldier Emmanuel Jal describes how he feels about the birth of South Sudan. Also South Korean film-maker Park Jung-Bum talks about fulfilling the dying wish of his North Korean friend, Jeon Seung-Chul. And the Vietnamese polio sufferer, Vo Thi Hoang Yen who's overcome prejudice to become a champion for people with disabilities with her organisation Disability Resource and Development (DRD). Show less